      • javaTypeName

        public java.lang.String javaTypeName()
        Obtains fully-qualified canonical name of the Java class that corresponds to the declared type of the field.

        If the field is repeated, obtains the name of the elements.

        If the field is a map, obtains the name of the values.

      • isEntityId

        public boolean isEntityId()
        Determines whether the field is an entity ID.

        An entity ID satisfies the following conditions:

        • Declared as the first field.
        • Declared inside an entity state message.
        • Is not a map or a repeated field.
        Returns:
        true if the field is an entity ID, false otherwise
        See Also:
        isId()

      • isId

        public boolean isId()
        Determines whether the field is an ID.

        An ID satisfies the following conditions:

        • Declared as the first field.
        • Declared inside an entity state message or a command message;
        • Is not a map or a repeated field.
        Returns:
        true if the field is an entity ID, false otherwise
